  "content": {
    "prompt": "<div><div class=\"stimulus_reference\"><div class=\"standalone_image\"><img alt=\"The figure shows three spheres labeled Sphere 1, Sphere 2, and Sphere 3. Each of the spheres has a charge of positive Q. Sphere 1 and Sphere 3 are the same size. Sphere 2 is larger than the other spheres.\" src=\"/images/bafef0d227c373522e3e81fe626133b3.svg\"></div></div></div><p class=\"stem_paragraph\">Three conducting spheres each have charge <span class=\"math_expression\"><span aria-label=\"positive Q\"><math alttext=\"positive Q\" display=\"inline\" overflow=\"scroll\"><mstyle displaystyle=\"true\"><mo>+</mo><mi>Q</mi></mstyle></math></span></span>. Spheres <span class=\"math_expression\"><span aria-label=\"1\"><math alttext=\"1\" display=\"inline\" overflow=\"scroll\"><mn>1</mn></math></span></span> and <span class=\"math_expression\"><span aria-label=\"3\"><math alttext=\"3\" display=\"inline\" overflow=\"scroll\"><mn>3</mn></math></span></span> have the same radius, while Sphere <span class=\"math_expression\"><span aria-label=\"2\"><math alttext=\"2\" display=\"inline\" overflow=\"scroll\"><mn>2</mn></math></span></span> has a larger radius. Sphere <span class=\"math_expression\"><span aria-label=\"1\"><math alttext=\"1\" display=\"inline\" overflow=\"scroll\"><mn>1</mn></math></span></span> is brought in contact with Sphere <span class=\"math_expression\"><span aria-label=\"2\"><math alttext=\"2\" display=\"inline\" overflow=\"scroll\"><mn>2</mn></math></span></span>, the two spheres come to equilibrium, and then they are separated. Next, Sphere <span class=\"math_expression\"><span aria-label=\"2\"><math alttext=\"2\" display=\"inline\" overflow=\"scroll\"><mn>2</mn></math></span></span> is brought in contact with sphere <span class=\"math_expression\"><span aria-label=\"3\"><math alttext=\"3\" display=\"inline\" overflow=\"scroll\"><mn>3</mn></math></span></span>, the two spheres come to equilibrium, and then they are separated. Which of the following correctly compares the electric potential <span class=\"math_expression\"><span aria-label=\"V sub 1\"><math alttext=\"V sub 1\" display=\"inline\" overflow=\"scroll\"><mstyle displaystyle=\"true\"><msub><mi>V</mi><mn>1</mn></msub></mstyle></math></span></span>, <span class=\"math_expression\"><span aria-label=\"V sub 2\"><math alttext=\"V sub 2\" display=\"inline\" overflow=\"scroll\"><mstyle displaystyle=\"true\"><msub><mi>V</mi><mn>2</mn></msub></mstyle></math></span></span>, <span class=\"math_expression\"><span aria-label=\"V sub 3\"><math alttext=\"V sub 3\" display=\"inline\" overflow=\"scroll\"><mstyle displaystyle=\"true\"><msub><mi>V</mi><mn>3</mn></msub></mstyle></math></span></span> at the surface of each sphere at the end of the described procedure?</p>\n",
    "answer": "i3",
